Works great on my Galaxy S6. The head tracking using your phone's sensors is a feature that no other software seems provide for some strange reason, but this software provides an excellent implementation of it that works amazingly with most games, no need to fuss with webcam tracking software.  If playback is choppy, use your USB cord, set your phone to USB tether mode, activate TrinusVR and set video output to Moonlight mode, and in the Moonlight menu on your phone, enter the "IPv6 Address" of TrinusVR, you can find it by opening "command prompt" on windows and typing "ipconfig" and hitting enter. Now you can launch games from your phone and they will play back buttery smooth and low latency!  I hope this app continues to improve and improve :)

replyContent:
If you stream a 4:3 ratio image to take half the display (8:9) there will be distortion (8/3 is not equal to 16/9). The app lets you adjust scaling or even crop the content to ensure proper ratio.
As for image quality, that very much depends on the quality setting you are using, which you'd need to tweak to get a good speed vs quality balance.

If you've tried the demo and it works for you, then I can guarantee you this app is worth the purchase!

For a solo development this app is amazing. It works fantastically well on nearly everything I've thrown at it, with exceptions being due to game/app interaction incompatibility at this stage of development. Trinus Gyre has the sort of usefulness that should be licensed by all o.s. makers to be included as standard with their products.

Works better than any other app like this.  By better, I mean less lag, more options built in.  Still a little rough around the edges, but that doesn't detract from the 5 star rating. If the basic app is this good, I can't wait for future updates!
Excellent
Works really well! Happy to buy this app and help this developer.
I would love a way to transmit the images over usb cable instead of the local network, and a way of just displaying two rectangular images instead of two curved images! Other than that great!
replyContent: USB connection is on the way :) and you can disable the curve with the lens toggle button.

content: Great app. App and server is easy to set up and to tweak. Tested it working with HL2 with good results. Slight lag in responsiveness but it's to be expected considering what's going on. Could you add saving and loading of customisable presets to help with the configuration on a per game basis?

More than glad to pay for a cutting edge app/service like this. It's rough around the edges, but that's exactly what I expected. Hopefully with  support and time some improvements can be made. If you've already gone through the trouble to build a diy oculus rift/google cardboard or bought a durovis dive I can't recommend grabbing this program enough. Keep at it!
